OL,6,FThree women who say they weren't
OL,7,Fwarned that their epilepsy medication
OL,8,Frisked causing birth defects in their
OL,9,Fchildren say they feel 'abandoned and
OL,10,Fforgotten' by the government.
OL,12,FCarole McNeil, Penny Johnson and Jo
OL,13,FGamblin all had babies with a variety
OL,14,Fof problems including mobility
OL,15,Fdifficulties, learning disabilities,
OL,16,Fspeech problems and autism.
OL,18,FThey gave birth to their now grown up
OL,19,Fchildren over a sixteen year time span
OL,20,F- but they all say they weren't told
OL,21,Fabout the dangers of sodium valproate.
