OL,4,Cled to birth defects feel 'abandoned'
OL,6,FWomen took the epilepsy medication to
OL,7,Fcontrol their seizures but say they
OL,8,Fweren't given the opportunity to
OL,9,Fswitch to alternatives and had no idea
OL,10,Fthe drug increased the risk of birth
OL,11,Fdefects and developmental delays.
OL,13,FPenny Johnson's son Alan was born ten
OL,14,Fyears after Sarah in 1999. He has
OL,15,Fmobility problems and autism.
OL,17,F"There was no warnings on the box,"
OL,18,Fsaid Penny. "Nothing said that I
OL,19,Fshouldn't take the medication before
OL,20,Ftrying for a baby. There was nothing."
