OL,3,CMothers who took epilepsy drug that
OL,4,Cled to birth defects feel 'abandoned'
OL,6,F"They've known for years the dangers
OL,7,Fof it," said Jo. " And to just leave
OL,8,Fwomen to carry on having children. I
OL,9,Fjust don't understand how they can
OL,10,Feven sleep at night."
OL,12,FJo's son Lewis is aged 19 and was born
OL,13,Fwith signs of sodium valproate
OL,14,Fsyndrome and has now been diagnosed
OL,15,Fwith ADHD and autism and registered as
OL,16,Fdisabled.
OL,18,F"What I really want to get across is
OL,19,Fwhat has happened to our children,"
OL,20,Fsaid Jo. "They need help.
