OL,6,F"In the 70s and 80s, few medicines
OL,7,Fwere supplied with any printed
OL,8,Finformation for patients.
OL,10,F"The first patient information leaflet
OL,11,Ffor valproate, approved in 1989,
OL,12,Fadvised patients to contact their
OL,13,Fdoctor if pregnant or planning a
OL,14,Fpregnancy so risks could be discussed."
OL,16,FIn 2018 new warnings were added to
OL,17,Fboxes of sodium valproate warning that
OL,18,Fthe drug shouldn't be taken by
OL,19,Fpregnant women.
